{"id": "duc04-testb-48:4#14", "contents": "Blair's visit has drawn appeals from dissidents and international organizations, including an open letter from three dissidents urging him to persuade Chinese leaders to free political prisoners. Thousands of political prisoners are believed to remain in Chinese prisons, labor camps, or detention centers. The letter calls for the release of several imprisoned activists, including Shi Binhai, a journalist who compiled a book on political change, and Fang Jue, a businessman who called openly for political reform. Reporters Without Borders has also urged Blair to call for the release of three journalists, Gao Yu, Liu Xiaobo, and Liu Jingsheng, who are among 13 imprisoned \"simply for attempting to practice their profession.\""}
